          "note": "Burnham's first film as writer-director; Fisher plays Kayla. He wanted a movie about \"now,\" not a nostalgia piece, and cast a girl to keep from projecting his own past onto her. Fisher was past eighth grade when they shot: 27 days, nine-hour days because she was 13. Burnham tested her seven times; the pool-party walk and the closed-set banana scene came up as the moments that read far more intense onscreen than they were to shoot."
